# Example entry:
{"id":"gotcha-example-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"Example: Truthy check on numeric values fails for explicit zero - if (value) is false when value === 0.","recommendation":"Use !== undefined or !== null instead of truthy checks when the value could legitimately be 0 or empty string.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"coderabbit","reference":"PR review","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["javascript","type-coercion","validation"],"affectedFiles":["**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-join-id-collision","type":"gotcha","fact":"SELECT p.*, pr.content FROM posts p JOIN post_revisions pr overwrites pr.id with p.id since both tables have an id column. The revision UUID is silently lost.","recommendation":"Always alias the secondary table PK: SELECT p.*, pr.id AS revision_id, pr.content ... and add revision_id to the row type.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #16 adversarial review","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["postgresql","join","id-collision","posts","revisions"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/db/queries/posts.ts","packages/server/src/db/queries/types.ts"],"affectedServices":["findPostWithLatestRevision"],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-sfc-dom-types","type":"gotcha","fact":"ESLint no-undef rule does not recognize DOM types (Event, HTMLSelectElement, HTMLInputElement) in Vue <script setup> blocks because the browser env is not configured.","recommendation":"Use /* global Event */ comment at the top of the function block, then cast event.target inside the handler: const target = event.target as unknown as { value: string }.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #16 pre-commit hook failures","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vue","eslint","dom-types","script-setup"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/components/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-template-ts-casts","type":"gotcha","fact":"TypeScript as casts cannot be used inline in Vue templates — e.g. ($event.target as HTMLSelectElement).value causes parse errors in vue-tsc.","recommendation":"Handle all type narrowing in <script> block functions, not in template expressions. Pass the cast result to the handler function.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #16 vue-tsc errors","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vue","typescript","template","vue-tsc"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/components/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-sfc-window-globals","type":"gotcha","fact":"ESLint no-undef does not recognize window/matchMedia/navigator in Vue <script setup>. The project uses typed declare statements rather than eslint-disable.","recommendation":"Add `declare const window: { specificMethod: ... }` at top of <script setup> with only the methods actually used. Do not use `/* eslint-disable no-undef */`.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #17 pre-commit failures in AppLayout, HomePage, PostListItem","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vue","eslint","no-undef","window","browser-globals"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-no-dupe-keys-composable","type":"gotcha","fact":"When a composable returns refs named the same as component props (e.g. sort, filter), Vue ESLint vue/no-dupe-keys flags a collision even though they are different variables.","recommendation":"Rename destructured composable refs to avoid collision: `const { sort: currentSort, filter: currentFilter } = useFeed()`.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #17 HomePage.vue lint failure","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vue","eslint","no-dupe-keys","composables","props"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/pages/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-v8-finally-coverage","type":"gotcha","fact":"Vitest with V8 coverage provider reports finally blocks as uncovered branches even when both try and catch paths execute. This is a V8 instrumentation artifact, not a real coverage gap.","recommendation":"Move cleanup statements (e.g. loading.value = false) into both try and catch paths instead of using finally. This satisfies the 100% branch threshold without losing behavior.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #18 Task 7 coverage gate","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["vitest","coverage","v8","finally","branch-coverage"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/composables/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-sfc-browser-globals","type":"gotcha","fact":"ESLint no-undef rule does not recognize setTimeout, clearTimeout, or window in Vue <script setup> blocks. Using window.setTimeout also fails because window itself is undefined to ESLint.","recommendation":"Add /* global setTimeout, clearTimeout */ at the top of the <script setup> block. See PostEditPage.vue and CodeViewer.vue for the established pattern.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #18 Task 8 pre-commit hook failure","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["eslint","vue","sfc","browser-globals","setTimeout"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/components/**/*.vue","packages/client/src/pages/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-plain-var-in-computed","type":"gotcha","fact":"A Vue computed reading a plain `let` variable will NOT re-evaluate when that variable mutates — it only re-evaluates when one of its tracked reactive dependencies (refs/reactive objects) changes. The computed may return stale data after a non-reactive write.","recommendation":"Anything a computed reads must be a ref (or reactive). In composables that mutate internal state between setup calls (e.g., `activeChannel` switching with postId), use `const x = ref<...>(null)` and read via `x.value` — never `let x`. A regression test that changes the variable and asserts the computed without triggering another reactive write will catch the bug.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 WU-008 adversarial review","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["vue","reactivity","composables","ref","computed"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/composables/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-fastify-plugin-major-version","type":"gotcha","fact":"@fastify/* plugins are pinned per Fastify major version. @fastify/websocket v10 targets Fastify 4 and depends on fastify-plugin@^4; v11 targets Fastify 5 and depends on fastify-plugin@^5. Installing the wrong major triggers a fastify-plugin version conflict at registration.","recommendation":"Before installing any @fastify/* plugin, check the current Fastify major in packages/server/package.json and pin the plugin to the matching line (Fastify 5 -> v11). This applies to every @fastify/* plugin, not just websocket.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 WU-005 plan review gate","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["fastify","dependencies","versioning","plugins"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/package.json"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-ws-types-peer-dep","type":"gotcha","fact":"Importing `WebSocket` (as a value OR as `import type`) from the `ws` package requires @types/ws as a devDependency. @fastify/websocket reexports the ws types via `import { WebSocket } from '@fastify/websocket'` but a direct `from 'ws'` import fails typecheck with TS7016 unless @types/ws is installed.","recommendation":"Either: (a) import WebSocket from '@fastify/websocket' which carries its own types, or (b) add @types/ws as a devDep to the server package. Prefer (a) to avoid an extra dep.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 WU-005 validation","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["typescript","fastify","websocket","types","ws"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/websocket/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-bruno-recursive-alphabetical-order","type":"gotcha","fact":"`npx @usebruno/cli run -r` walks directories in alphabetical order, not in a logical dependency order. Tests that depend on env vars set by post-response scripts in earlier requests (e.g., commentId set by create-comment, postId set by create-post) will fail when directories earlier in the alphabet need vars set by later ones — e.g., bookmarks/comments run BEFORE posts, so {{postId}} is empty and routes return 500.","recommendation":"For regression runs, invoke dependency directories in order: `bruno run auth && bruno run posts && bruno run comments && bruno run votes`. The `-r` shorthand is only safe for directories with no inter-directory var dependencies.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #1 WU-006 final verification","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["bruno","testing","api","ordering"],"affectedFiles":["bruno/**/*.bru"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-zod-coerce-boolean-querystring","type":"gotcha","fact":"z.coerce.boolean() silently misreads the string 'false' as true because any non-empty string is truthy in JavaScript. Any Zod schema that validates query-string booleans with z.coerce.boolean() will accept ?fuzzy=false and decode it as { fuzzy: true }, producing the opposite of the intended semantics.","recommendation":"For Zod fields that come from query strings and must round-trip a real boolean, use z.preprocess((v) => typeof v === 'string' ? v === 'true' : v, z.boolean()) instead of z.coerce.boolean(). Real booleans pass through; strings 'true' and 'false' coerce correctly; other strings decode as false. Unit-test both the 'true' and 'false' string cases.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 WU-2 search query schema","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["zod","validation","boolean","query-string","schema"],"affectedFiles":["packages/shared/src/types/**/*.ts","packages/shared/src/validators/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-multi-word-page-name","type":"gotcha","fact":"Vue ESLint rule vue/multi-word-component-names fails the pre-commit hook for any single-word component filename such as Search.vue, Post.vue, or Feed.vue. The rule triggers on the filename inferred as the component name, not just <name> declarations.","recommendation":"Follow the project's established *Page.vue naming convention for page components (HomePage.vue, LoginPage.vue, SearchPage.vue, PostViewPage.vue). For non-page components, pick any two-word name (e.g. UserAvatar, PostDetail). If you must keep a one-word name, add a `name:` export in <script> that is multi-word.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 WU-11 pre-commit failure","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["vue","eslint","component-naming","pages","pre-commit"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/pages/**/*.vue","packages/client/src/components/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-non-null-assertion-in-tests","type":"gotcha","fact":"@typescript-eslint/no-non-null-assertion is enforced in TEST files too, not only source — wrapper.emitted('select')![0] fails the pre-commit hook. The rule applies everywhere because tests share the base ESLint config.","recommendation":"Replace test-file non-null assertions with optional chaining: wrapper.emitted('select')?.[0]. Combined with toHaveLength(1) on the preceding line, optional chaining is as safe as `!` and passes the lint gate. Do not suppress the rule with eslint-disable.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 WU-9 pre-commit failure","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["eslint","tests","non-null-assertion","vue-test-utils","optional-chaining"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/__tests__/**/*.ts","packages/server/src/__tests__/**/*.ts","packages/shared/src/__tests__/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-fastify-onrequest-before-prehandler-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"Fastify lifecycle runs onRequest BEFORE preHandler. app.authenticate is registered as a preHandler decorator, so request.user is still undefined inside an onRequest hook.","recommendation":"Auth-gated rate limiters, audit hooks, and anything that reads request.user must run as a preHandler (after authenticate). Compose with [app.authenticate, customHook]; never use onRequest for post-auth logic.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["fastify","lifecycle","auth","jwt"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/**/*.ts","packages/server/src/routes/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-defineexpose-shallowref-unwrap-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"When a Vue 3 child does defineExpose({ view: shallowRef(...) }), the parent accesses the value as childRef.value.view (ref is auto-unwrapped one level). Writing childRef.value.view.value returns undefined and TypeScript does not catch it because the expose types preserve the ref shape.","recommendation":"In the parent, destructure/use the exposed ref without an extra .value: computed(() => editorRef.value?.view ?? null). Verify via a test that mounts the real child and asserts the computed resolves.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["vue3","refs","defineExpose","shallowRef"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":["client"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-langchain-prompt-brace-escape-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"LangChain ChatPromptTemplate treats { and } in message content as variable delimiters. Literal braces (e.g., in few-shot code examples: \"function foo() {\") throw \"Missing variable\" on invoke/stream.","recommendation":"Escape every literal brace in prompt strings as {{ and }}. Applies to system messages, human messages, and few-shot examples that contain code snippets.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["langchain","prompts","templates"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/plugins/langchain/prompts/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-langchain-fake-pipe-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"Testing createChain(fakeModel) by giving a fake BaseChatModel its own .pipe() method does NOT work, because prompt.pipe(model).pipe(parser) is routed through a RunnableSequence that never calls the injected model's pipe — it calls model.invoke/model.stream directly.","recommendation":"For chain-construction tests: use FakeListChatModel from @langchain/core/utils/testing (a real BaseChatModel). For chain-iteration tests: mock the Runnable chain's .stream() directly with an object that returns an async iterable. Do not try to intercept pipe().","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["langchain","testing","runnables"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/__tests__/plugins/langchain/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":["server"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vitest-v8-nullish-branch-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"Vitest v8 coverage counts ?? (nullish-coalescing) and ||/&& branches. Writing \"language: props.language ?? 'plaintext'\" when language is a required (non-optional) prop creates an unreachable right-side branch that silently drops branch coverage below 100%.","recommendation":"Remove dead null-coalescing fallbacks when the type system guarantees the left side is defined. Trust the type contract; don't hedge with defensive defaults that can never fire.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["vitest","coverage","typescript","v8"],"affectedFiles":["packages/**/*.{ts,vue}"],"affectedServices":["client","server","shared"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-husky-post-failure-staging-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"If a git commit fails in a husky pre-commit hook (e.g. lint error), the staged files remain staged. A subsequent \"git add differentFiles && git commit\" silently pulls in the earlier staged files, combining two logical commits into one.","recommendation":"After a husky hook failure, either finish the fix and re-commit the same intended set, OR run git reset HEAD -- <previously-staged-files> to unstage them before staging a different change. Verify with git diff --cached before every commit.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"issue #9 LangChain AI autocomplete","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["git","husky","hooks"],"affectedFiles":[],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-bruno-silent-pass","type":"gotcha","fact":"Bruno CLI (@usebruno/cli) run -r reports '✓ PASS' even when HTTP requests return 5xx or 4xx, as long as no tests{} or assert{} block exists in the .bru file. The summary counts a request as failed only if an explicit status assertion fails.","recommendation":"Every .bru file MUST include an assert{} or tests{} block asserting the expected status. CI must lint-fail if any .bru file lacks an assertion block BEFORE running the suite.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #28 resolution","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["bruno","testing","regression-gate","silent-failure"],"affectedFiles":["bruno/**/*.bru"],"affectedServices":["bruno-regression-ci"],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-tsc-narrow-consumer-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"A Vue SFC that consumes a NARROWER type than `@forge/shared`'s exported type (e.g. AI generation accepts `snippet|prompt|document` but ContentType is `snippet|prompt|document|link`) fails vue-tsc TS2322 when it types its prop with the wide shared type and then passes the prop into a function expecting the narrow type.","recommendation":"Derive the prop type from the narrow source rather than the wide shared enum. For Zod-backed schemas use `import type { AiGenerateRequest } from '@forge/shared'` and type the prop as `AiGenerateRequest['contentType']` — this auto-syncs with the schema and prevents wide→narrow type leaks. The parent renders a v-if guard (e.g. `v-if='isAiGenerateContentType'`) so runtime matches the type.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"Issue #10 WU-006 vue-tsc failure + WU-007 integration","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["vue","vue-tsc","typescript","zod","narrow-type","props"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/components/**/*.vue","packages/shared/src/validators/**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-vue-tsc-template-vif-narrowing-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"vue-tsc does NOT narrow a bound child-component prop's type based on a template v-if guard on the same element. `<AiGeneratePanel v-if='isNarrow' :content-type='contentType' />` still sees `contentType` as the wide union — the v-if does not reach the type checker for the binding.","recommendation":"Cast at the binding site after the v-if: `:content-type='contentType as AiGenerateContentType'` where the local alias resolves to the narrow enum. Runtime safety comes from the v-if condition (e.g. `Set.has(exactLiterals)`); the cast just tells vue-tsc what the runtime already guarantees. Avoid `as any` — use the exact narrow alias.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"self-reflect","reference":"Issue #10 WU-007 PostEditor integration","date":"2026-04-14"}],"tags":["vue","vue-tsc","typescript","template","type-narrowing","v-if"],"affectedFiles":["packages/client/src/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
